			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008 SI</a> paper:</span><br><i>A Model-Based Approach to Families of Embedded Domain-Specific Languages</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/JesúsSánchezCuadrado.html">Jesús Sánchez Cuadrado</a>, <a href="../profile/JesúsGarćıaMolina.html">Jesús Garćıa Molina</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1109/TSE.2009.14">10.1109/TSE.2009.14</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1e.html"><span class="tagM">T1E: Reuse</span></a><ul><li> The main contribution is a reuse-oriented approach to build families of embedded DSLs via systematic composition mechanisms.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2c.html"><span class="tagL">T2C: Variability</span></a><ul><li> It explicitly treats “families of DSLs” and variability through composing and configuring multiple DSL definitions.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> The approach centres on composition of abstract syntax, concrete syntax, and transformations, i.e., modular combination of language artefacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> Embedded DSLs are the target language form and the paper contributes a framework and case study for engineering them.
</li></ul></li></ul>
